<Desc><entry>Weston Park is a modern museum where visitors and not the stuffed animals are the most important creatures.  There is plenty of interest to children and adults alike.  Discover the story of Sheffield from its geological roots to the people, politics and music that shaped the modern city.  With collections spanning from the historical Benty Grange Helmet to the visitors favorite, Snowy the polar bear, alongside a programme of changing exhibitions.  Facilities include cafe, shop, lockers and toilets.  Free children's activities at weekends and holiday periods.</entry>
